text: The Unity Chapel is in the town of Wyoming in Iowa County, Wisconsin. It was added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1974. ==History== The Unitarian chapel was designed for Jenkin Lloyd Jones, a Unitarian minister from Wales. Jones' nephew, Frank Lloyd Wright, worked on the project. ==References== Category:Churches in the United States Category:Frank Lloyd Wright Category:1886 establishments in the United States Category:1880s establishments in Wisconsin
